Definition.WordDefinition: Reestablishment \Re`["e]s*tab"lish*ment\ (-mnt), n. The act re["e]stablishing; the state of being re["e]stablished. --Addison. [1913 Webster]
re-establishment n : restoration to a previous state; "regular exercise resulted in the re-establishment of his endurance"
